                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4708b.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-08-21T15:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1912—3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s 907, of July 19. <hi rend="italic">Vicksburg</hi>, which sailed from
                    San Diego August 22, will proceed first to Guaymas, arriving there about August
                    28, and later proceed to the other west-coast ports in her itinerary. So inform
                    Mexican Government.</p>
                <p>In view of the situation that has arisen in Sonora the <hi rend="italic"
                        >Vicksburg</hi> has secret orders to remain at Guaymas for the protection of
                    American citizens and American interests in that region until it is possible to
                    foresee with more or less certainty what will be the course of events.</p>
                <p>The <hi rend="italic">Des Moines</hi> will make a casual visit to the east-coast
                    ports similar to that outlined for the west coast, and will start some time <pb
                        facs="0944" n="828" xml:id="pg_828"/> during the first week in September,
                    going first to Tampico, and touching later at Vera Cruz and Progreso, and
                    possibly at Coatzacoalcos. You will be informed of itinerary later. Make same
                    representations to the Mexican Government for her as for <hi rend="italic"
                        >Vicksburg.</hi>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Huntington Wilson.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
